# EZ Manual Simplifier - Environment Variables Example

## LLM API Keys

# Gemini API Key (Primary)
# Get from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# OpenAI API Key (Fallback)
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

## Cloudflare Workers

# Cloudflare API Token
# Get from: https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your_cloudflare_api_token_here

# Cloudflare Account ID
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your_account_id_here

## GitHub Secrets Configuration

# These values should be set in GitHub Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 
# Required Secrets:
# - GEMINI_API_KEY
# - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
# - OPENAI_API_KEY (optional)
#
# How to set:
# 1. Go to: https://github.com/kazu-4728/ez-manual-simplifier/settings/secrets/actions
# 2. Click "New repository secret"
# 3. Add each secret with its corresponding value

## Local Development

# For local development, copy this file to .env and fill in your values
# NEVER commit the .env file to the repository
# The .env file is in .gitignore

## Notes

# - Keep these keys secret
# - Rotate keys periodically
# - Use GitHub Secrets for production
# - Use .env only for local development
